    <text id="R1461065T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union General Winfield Scott Hancock writes General Torbert to order a May, 1865,
                    expedition to Staunton. Hancock orders Torbert to take blank paroles, and to
                    make sure all goods are paid for, and the property of civilians respected.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Brevet Maj.-Gen. TORBERT,<lb/> Cmdg. Army of the
                        Shenandoah:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-05-01">May 1, 1865</date>--<time>5 p.m.</time>
                        <name type="place">WASHINGTON, D. C.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>GEN.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I wish to send an expedition to Staunton with twenty-five days' rations,
                    consisting of one brigade of infantry, under a good commander. I would suggest
                    Gen. Duval. I also wish Brig.-Gen. Carroll to be ready to march here through
                    Loudoun County, with his three regiments of veterans, to join the remainder at
                    Camp Stoneman. I will send you orders in detail. Have them ready. I also wish a
                    good regiment of cavalry to go with the brigade to Staunton. Blank paroles
                    should be sent with the command, and all regular supplies should be paid for, or
                    proper vouchers given. The greatest order should be preserved in the marches,
                    and no depredations upon private property whatever should be permitted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, very respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>W. S. HANCOCK,<lb/> Maj.-Gen., Cmdg. Middle Military Division.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
